    <item>
      <title>Typing Unicode Characters in Ubuntu</title>
      <link>http://www.sahil.cc/post/2017/typing-unicode-characters-in-ubuntu/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Aug 2017 23:20:16 +0530</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.sahil.cc/post/2017/typing-unicode-characters-in-ubuntu/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Ever since I decided that &lt;code&gt;&amp;#96;&lt;/code&gt; was he best means to toggle Yakuake (which has been my lifeline for an integral part of the way I work for a long time now), typing &lt;code&gt;&amp;#96;&lt;/code&gt; whenever I needed it has been hell.

After going through a great deal and self doubt, the final outcome deserves being documented.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
